<p class="comment-body">Jen,Sunderland.
Meditation is not a quick fix panacea,but rather something which takes much practice and patience. A way to explain it is like learning to play a musical instrument, you can spend time practiceing seemingly pointless laborious scales. Yet, after much disipline everything falls into place, and the benefits are boundless. Give it a try, you may surprise yourself.</p>
<p class="user-info bold">- Geoff Wall-Davis,, Longbridge, Birmingham, England., 17/8/2010 16:35</p>
