<div class="comment-post bogr1 bdrgr3 cleared">
<p class="comment-body">Meditation is a technique begging to be explored for its potential health benefits. It's already been proven as an effective method for reducing blood pressure, increasing T-cell count, treating anxiety and depression - the list goes on, look it up.
It isn't new age clap trap or spiritual mumbo jumbo - it's the skill of quieting your mind, honing your concentration and being fully aware of your thoughts and bodily sensations. It leads to greater compassion and wisdom. Why this isn't part of the national curriculum is beyond me.</p>
<p class="user-info bold">- granty, liverpool, 17/8/2010 14:08</p>
